{"TopicId":195149,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Pan up and down in launch mode","CreatedByName":"KrisKelvin","CreatedById":204872,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-29T18:57:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KrisKelvin","CreatedById":204872,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-29T18:57:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E I can pan up and down with the mouse wheel. But this doesn\u0027t work on the launch pad. How can I pan up and down there?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-29T23:22:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing exactly like in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E but\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) you can \u0022Aim camera\u0022 from the right--click menu so that the camera is centered on that part; select again to toggle back to centering the view on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) you can pan the camera aiming with hold-middle-mouse-button and drag,\u00A0then a double-middle-click resets the aiming to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E or the part chosen as above (see KSPedia under mouse controls).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI \u003Cem\u003Eguess\u003C/em\u003E the first one will be more useful for what you want --- and hope someone else knows an even easier way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-30T04:26:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223811612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022195149\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221593472928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OHara\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, OHara said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0and hope someone else knows an even easier way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na Mod.\u00A0Highly probable to be\u00A0overkill for what the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E needs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KrisKelvin","CreatedById":204872,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-30T16:46:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223811612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022195149\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221593472928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OHara\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, OHara said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing exactly like in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E but\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) you can \u0022Aim camera\u0022 from the right--click menu so that the camera is centered on that part; select again to toggle back to centering the view on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) you can pan the camera aiming with hold-middle-mouse-button and drag,\u00A0then a double-middle-click resets the aiming to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E or the part chosen as above (see KSPedia under mouse controls).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI \u003Cem\u003Eguess\u003C/em\u003E the first one will be more useful for what you want --- and hope someone else knows an even easier way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you say \u0022right click menu\u0022 what do you mean? If I right click, I get nothing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-30T21:50:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight mouse-click with the pointer over a part.\u00A0 I see it called the\u00A0Part Action Window (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003EPAW\u003C/abbr\u003E) in this forum, but the KSPedia just says right button click\u00A0\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage ipsAttachLink_image ipsAttachLink_right\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.45\u0022 height=\u0022620\u0022 style=\u0022width:440px;height:auto;float:right;\u0022 width=\u0022880\u0022 alt=\u0022md8mmQe.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/md8mmQe.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KrisKelvin","CreatedById":204872,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-07-02T09:43:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223812140\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022195149\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221593553829\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OHara\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/30/2020 at 10:50 PM, OHara said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight mouse-click with the pointer over a part.\u00A0 I see it called the\u00A0Part Action Window (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003EPAW\u003C/abbr\u003E) in this forum, but the KSPedia just says right button click\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/md8mmQe.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022md8mmQe.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsAttachLink_image ipsAttachLink_right ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.45\u0022 height=\u0022620\u0022 style=\u0022width:440px;height:auto;float:right;\u0022 width=\u0022880\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/md8mmQe.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm.. that\u0027s strange. I don\u0027t get that menu if I right mouse click over a part.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am on 1.9.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I can seem to move the viewpoint a bit by holding down the mousewheel as a button and moving the mouse. Thanks for that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-07-02T13:13:32Z\u0022 title=\u002207/02/2020 01:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 2, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by KrisKelvin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}